      • isFirstLineAsSchema

        public boolean isFirstLineAsSchema()
        Is set to true when the first line of the input text contains the names and order of the cells in the following lines, i.e. the first line is a header line. In that case this schema line instance will only be used to get formatting instructions and default values, it will not denote the order of the cells. The order is given by the first line of the input instead.
        Returns:
        true when the first line of the input text contains the names and order of the cells in the following, false otherwise.

      • setFirstLineAsSchema

        public void setFirstLineAsSchema(boolean firstLineAsSchema)
        Set this to true when the first line of the input text contains the names and order of the cells in the following lines, i.e. the first line is a header line that works as a schema for the rest of the file. In that case this schema line instance will only be used to get formatting instructions and default values, it will not denote the order of the cells. The order is given by the first line of the input instead.
        Parameters:
        firstLineAsSchema - Set to true when the first line of the input text contains the names and order of the cells in the following lines.
